# API and UI

## Server (`apps/server`)

- Keep route handlers thin — validate input, call `services/` or `core`, return JSON
- Split routes by domain under `src/routes/` (e.g. `projects.ts`, `scan.ts`); wire in `routes/index.ts`
- Shared adapter helpers live in `src/adapters.ts`; data loading in `src/services/`
- Validate request bodies with Zod when non-trivial
- Return JSON errors: `{ error: string, code: string }`
- CORS: allow only `localhost` origins in dev
- Avoid monolithic `app.ts` — target ~50 lines for composition only

## Web (`apps/web`)

### Services layer (required)

- **No `fetch` in components or hooks that render UI** — all HTTP lives in `src/services/`
- Services call `http-client.ts` (`getJson` / `postJson`); one service file per domain (`projects-service`, `records-service`, `scan-service`)
- Components and containers import from `@/services`, never `@/api`

### Container vs presentational (required)

- **Container** (`*-container.tsx` or `use-*.ts` hook): state, side effects, service calls, derived data
- **Presentational** (`*-view.tsx`, panel components): props in, JSX out; no service imports
- Split when a file exceeds ~200 lines or mixes data loading with layout
- Extract a sub-component only when it is a coherent UI section (header, sidebar panel, detail view) — not one-off wrappers

### File layout example

```
src/
  services/           # HTTP + API shapes
  hooks/              # container logic (useMemoryBrowser)
  components/
    memory-browser/
      memory-browser-container.tsx
      memory-browser-view.tsx
      projects-panel.tsx
      records-panel.tsx
```

### UI behaviour

- Show severity badges for scan findings: error / warning / info
- Editor: warn before save if record is `writable: false`
- Never store memory content in `localStorage`

## UX priorities

1. Health Scan results — primary screen after project select
2. Session Preview — secondary panel or tab
3. Raw file browser — tertiary; collapsible

## Accessibility

- Keyboard navigable scan results list
- Sufficient contrast on severity colors
